WITH date_gen AS (
    





with rawdata as (

    

    

    with p as (
        select 0 as generated_number union all select 1
    ), unioned as (

    select

    
    p0.generated_number * power(2, 0)
     + 
    
    p1.generated_number * power(2, 1)
     + 
    
    p2.generated_number * power(2, 2)
     + 
    
    p3.generated_number * power(2, 3)
     + 
    
    p4.generated_number * power(2, 4)
     + 
    
    p5.generated_number * power(2, 5)
     + 
    
    p6.generated_number * power(2, 6)
     + 
    
    p7.generated_number * power(2, 7)
     + 
    
    p8.generated_number * power(2, 8)
     + 
    
    p9.generated_number * power(2, 9)
     + 
    
    p10.generated_number * power(2, 10)
     + 
    
    p11.generated_number * power(2, 11)
    
    
    + 1
    as generated_number

    from

    
    p as p0
     cross join 
    
    p as p1
     cross join 
    
    p as p2
     cross join 
    
    p as p3
     cross join 
    
    p as p4
     cross join 
    
    p as p5
     cross join 
    
    p as p6
     cross join 
    
    p as p7
     cross join 
    
    p as p8
     cross join 
    
    p as p9
     cross join 
    
    p as p10
     cross join 
    
    p as p11
    
    

    )

    select *
    from unioned
    where generated_number <= 2192
    order by generated_number



),

all_periods as (

    select (
        

    dateadd(
        day,
        row_number() over (order by 1) - 1,
        cast('2019-01-01' as date)
        )


    ) as date_day
    from rawdata

),

filtered as (

    select *
    from all_periods
    where date_day <= cast('2025-01-01' as date)

)

select * from filtered


),
company_gen AS (
     SELECT 'MSFT' AS company_name
     UNION ALL
     SELECT 'GOG' AS company_name
     UNION ALL
     SELECT 'AMZN' AS company_name
     UNION ALL
     SELECT 'A' AS company_name
     UNION ALL
     SELECT 'FB' AS company_name
),
country_gen AS (
    SELECT 'FR' AS country
    UNION ALL
    SELECT 'DE' AS country
    UNION ALL
    SELECT 'GB' AS country
    UNION ALL
    SELECT 'US' AS country
    UNION all

)

SELECT *, LENGTH(company_name)+LENGTH(country) AS str_length

SELECT
    country
    , SUM(str_length) AS sum_2_str_length
    -- example: sum
    , 




    ROUND(
      
        sum(str_length)
        /
        SUM(sum(str_length)) OVER ()
      
    , 3)
 AS sum_percent

    , COUNT(company_name) AS count_company_name
    -- example: count
    -- defaults to count if no aggregation function is specified and 1 decimal if no precision is specified

    , 




    ROUND(
      
        COUNT(company_name)
        /
        SUM(COUNT(company_name)) OVER ()
      
    , 3)
 AS count_percent

    , COUNT(DISTINCT company_name) AS count_distinct_company_name
    -- example: countdistinct
    , 




    ROUND(
      
      COUNT(DISTINCT company_name)
        /
        SUM(COUNT(DISTINCT company_name)) OVER ()
      
    , 3)
 AS count_distinct_percent

FROM dbt_db.dbt_schema.data_aggregated
GROUP BY 1
ORDER BY sum(str_length)  DESC

SELECT
    company_name
    , country
    , count(str_length) AS count_str_length
    -- the percentages are caclulated at the aggregation of company_name and not entire column
    , 



  


    ROUND(
      
        count(str_length)
        /
        SUM(count(str_length)) OVER (PARTITION BY company_name)
      
    , 3)
 AS count_percent

FROM dbt_db.dbt_schema.data_aggregated
GROUP BY 1,2
ORDER BY company_name, country, count(str_length)  DESC

WITH
percent_of_total AS (
    SELECT
        company_name
        , country
        , 




    ROUND(
      
        COUNT(str_length)
        /
        SUM(COUNT(str_length)) OVER ()
      
    , 3)
 AS count_percent
        , 



  


    ROUND(
      
        COUNT(str_length)
        /
        SUM(COUNT(str_length)) OVER (PARTITION BY company_name)
      
    , 3)
 AS count_percent_level

    FROM dbt_db.dbt_schema.data_aggregated
    GROUP BY 1,2
    ORDER BY company_name, country, sum(str_length)  DESC
)
SELECT * FROM percent_of_total
WHERE
    1=1
    -- aggregated percent at level is always greater than percent of entire column
    AND
    (
        count_percent_level < count_percent
    -- MSFT has 3 countries, so each should be 1/3 of the total
    OR (company_name = 'MSFT' AND count_percent_level <> .333)
    -- AMZN & FB are unfiltered and have 5 countries, so each should be 1/5 of the total
    OR (company_name IN ('AMZN','FB') AND count_percent_level <> .2)
    -- Each with 4 countries, so each should be 1/4 of the total
    OR (company_name IN ('GOG','A') AND count_percent_level <> .25)
    )

WITH
percent_of_total AS (
    SELECT
    country
    -- precision needs to be atleast 4 for the sum to be 100%
    , 




    ROUND(
      
        sum(str_length)
        /
        SUM(sum(str_length)) OVER ()
      
    , 4)
 AS sum_percent
    , 




    ROUND(
      
        count(company_name)
        /
        SUM(count(company_name)) OVER ()
      
    , 4)
 AS count_percent
    , 




    ROUND(
      
      COUNT(DISTINCT company_name)
        /
        SUM(COUNT(DISTINCT company_name)) OVER ()
      
    , 4)
 AS count_distinct_percent
    , 




    ROUND(
      
        NULL
      
    , 2)
 AS incorrect_returns_null

FROM dbt_db.dbt_schema.data_aggregated
GROUP BY 1
)
, sum_percent_of_total AS (
    SELECT
        sum(sum_percent) AS sum_percent
        , sum(count_percent) AS count_percent
        , sum(count_distinct_percent) AS count_distinct_percent
        , sum(incorrect_returns_null) AS incorrect_returns_null
    FROM percent_of_total
)
SELECT * FROM sum_percent_of_total
WHERE
    sum_percent<>1
    OR count_percent<>1
    OR count_distinct_percent<>1
    OR incorrect_returns_null IS NOT NULL

WITH
percent_of_total AS (
    SELECT
    country
    -- rounding defaults to 2 if unspecified
    , 




    ROUND(
      
        sum(str_length)
        /
        SUM(sum(str_length)) OVER ()
      
    , 2)
 AS sum_percent
    , 




    ROUND(
      
        sum(str_length)
        /
        SUM(sum(str_length)) OVER ()
      
    , 2)
 AS sum_percent_3

FROM dbt_db.dbt_schema.data_aggregated
GROUP BY 1
)
SELECT * FROM percent_of_total
WHERE
    country = 'GB'
    AND sum_percent <> 0.2
    AND sum_percent <> 0.24

/**
 * Retrieves the missing dates in the date_day column of the missing_day model at the Day level granularity.
 *
 * @param {string} missing_day - The name of the model.
 * @param {string} date_day - The name of the column containing the dates.
 * @param {array} [dimensions] - An optional array of dimensions across which the missing dates are computed.
 * @param {object} [filters] - An optional filter object.
 * @param {string} [expected_frequency] - The interval to use when generating the missing dates (e.g. 'DAY', 'MONTH', 'YEAR').
 * @returns {rows} Rows of missing dates.
 */


WITH
unique_dates AS (
  SELECT
    DISTINCT
        date_day
        
  FROM dbt_db.dbt_schema.missing_day
  
)
, dates_lagged AS (
  SELECT *
  , LAG(date_day,1) OVER (
        ORDER BY
        
        date_day DESC) AS next_date_day
  FROM unique_dates
)
SELECT
    date_day
    
    , next_date_day
    , ABS(datediff(
        DAY,
        next_date_day,
        date_day
        )) AS missing_day
FROM dates_lagged
WHERE datediff(
        DAY,
        next_date_day,
        date_day
        ) < -1

WITH
    
    
    
    
    meta_data AS (
        -- Need to explicitly cast the type before transposing the data
        SELECT
        column_name
        , data_type
        , COUNT(*) OVER ():: STRING AS nbr_of_columns
        , CASE
            
            WHEN DATA_TYPE IN ('VARCHAR','CHAR', 'CHARACTER', 'STRING', 'TEXT') THEN 'text'
            
            WHEN DATA_TYPE IN ('DATE','DATETIME','TIMESTAMP','TIMESTAMP_LTZ','TIMESTAMP_NTZ','TIMESTAMP_TZ') THEN 'date'
            
            WHEN DATA_TYPE IN ('NUMBER','DECIMAL','NUMERIC','INT','INTEGER','BIGINT','SMALLINT','FLOAT','FLOAT4','FLOAT8','DOUBLE','DOUBLE PRECISION','REAL','INT64', 'TINYINT','BYETEINT', 'BIGDECIMAL','FLOAT64') THEN 'numeric'
            
            WHEN DATA_TYPE IN ('BOOLEAN','BOOL') THEN 'boolean'
            
            WHEN DATA_TYPE IN ('TIME') THEN 'time'
            
        END AS data_type_input

        
            , COUNT_IF(DATA_TYPE IN ('VARCHAR','CHAR', 'CHARACTER', 'STRING', 'TEXT')) OVER () :: STRING  AS nbr_of_text_columns

        
            , COUNT_IF(DATA_TYPE IN ('DATE','DATETIME','TIMESTAMP','TIMESTAMP_LTZ','TIMESTAMP_NTZ','TIMESTAMP_TZ')) OVER () :: STRING  AS nbr_of_date_columns

        
            , COUNT_IF(DATA_TYPE IN ('NUMBER','DECIMAL','NUMERIC','INT','INTEGER','BIGINT','SMALLINT','FLOAT','FLOAT4','FLOAT8','DOUBLE','DOUBLE PRECISION','REAL','INT64', 'TINYINT','BYETEINT', 'BIGDECIMAL','FLOAT64')) OVER () :: STRING  AS nbr_of_numeric_columns

        
            , COUNT_IF(DATA_TYPE IN ('BOOLEAN','BOOL')) OVER () :: STRING  AS nbr_of_boolean_columns

        
            , COUNT_IF(DATA_TYPE IN ('TIME')) OVER () :: STRING  AS nbr_of_time_columns

        

        FROM INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLES t
        INNER JOIN INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS c ON
                c.table_schema = t.table_schema AND c.table_name = t.table_name
                WHERE t.table_name = 'DATA_GENERATOR_ENRICHED_DESCRIBE'
    )


    
    , 

    

        meta_data_unique AS (
            SELECT
                    DISTINCT
                    'dataset' AS identifier
                    , NULL AS detail
                    , nbr_of_columns
                    , nbr_of_text_columns
                    , nbr_of_date_columns
                    , nbr_of_numeric_columns
                    , nbr_of_boolean_columns
                    , nbr_of_time_columns
                FROM meta_data
        )
        , dataset_info AS (
            SELECT
                    CASE LOWER(meta_data_key)
                            WHEN 'nbr_of_columns' THEN 1
                            WHEN 'nbr_of_text_columns' THEN 2
                            WHEN 'nbr_of_date_columns' THEN 3
                            WHEN 'nbr_of_numeric_columns' THEN 4
                            WHEN 'nbr_of_boolean_columns' THEN 5
                            WHEN 'nbr_of_time_columns' THEN 6
                    END AS index_pos
                    , meta_data_key
                    , identifier
                    , detail
                    , meta_data_value:: STRING AS meta_data_value
                FROM meta_data_unique
                UNPIVOT (meta_data_value FOR meta_data_key IN (nbr_of_columns, nbr_of_text_columns, nbr_of_date_columns, nbr_of_numeric_columns,nbr_of_boolean_columns,nbr_of_time_columns))
        )

    


    
    , 

    
        rowcount_info AS (
            SELECT
                    0 AS index_pos
                    , UPPER('nbr_of_rows') AS meta_data_key
                    , 'dataset' AS identifier
                    , NULL AS detail
                    , COUNT(*):: STRING AS meta_data_value
            FROM dbt_db.dbt_schema.data_generator_enriched_describe
            GROUP BY ALL
        )
    


    
    , 

    
        column_info AS (
            SELECT
                20 + ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY data_type) AS index_pos
                , column_name AS meta_data_key
                , 'column' AS identifier
                , NULL AS detail
                , data_type:: STRING AS meta_data_value
            FROM meta_data
        )
    


    
    , 
    
    assembled_result AS (
        
            SELECT
                
                     index_pos
                
                    , meta_data_key
                
                    , meta_data_value
                
                    , identifier
                
                    , detail
                
            FROM
            dataset_info
            UNION ALL
        
            SELECT
                
                     index_pos
                
                    , meta_data_key
                
                    , meta_data_value
                
                    , identifier
                
                    , detail
                
            FROM

            UNION ALL
        
            SELECT
                
                     index_pos
                
                    , meta_data_key
                
                    , meta_data_value
                
                    , identifier
                
                    , detail
                
            FROM
            column_info
            
        
    )

    , 

    
    

    

    

    
    

    
    
        column_detail_COMPANY_NAME AS (
            SELECT
                1
                
                    , COMPANY_NAME
                    , COUNT(*) AS cnt
                


                , SUM(COUNT(COMPANY_NAME)) OVER () AS cnt_total
                , SUM(COUNT(DISTINCT COMPANY_NAME)) OVER () AS cnt_unique
                , COUNT_IF(COMPANY_NAME IS NULL) AS cnt_null

            FROM dbt_db.dbt_schema.data_generator_enriched_describe

        ) ,

                , SUM(COUNT(DISTINCT COUNTRY)) OVER () AS cnt_unique
                , COUNT_IF(COUNTRY IS NULL) AS cnt_null

            FROM dbt_db.dbt_schema.data_generator_enriched_describe

            GROUP BY ALL
            LIMIT 10
        )

                'column_name', 'COMPANY_NAME'
                , 'count' , MIN(cnt_total)
                , 'count_null' , MIN(cnt_null)
                
                    , 'unique' , MIN(cnt_unique)

            ) AS detail

                    , 'unique' , MIN(cnt_unique)
                    , 'value_counts_top10',OBJECT_AGG(COUNTRY, cnt)
                
            ) AS detail
        FROM column_detail_COUNTRY
        
    

    )

        FROM column_detail_STR_LENGTH
        
    

    )

    LEFT JOIN column_detail_info_numeric AS numeric_detail

    ORDER BY index_pos ASC

                    , COMPANY_NAME
                    , COUNT(*) AS cnt
                


                , SUM(COUNT(COMPANY_NAME)) OVER () AS cnt_total
                , SUM(COUNT(DISTINCT COMPANY_NAME)) OVER () AS cnt_unique
                , COUNT_IF(COMPANY_NAME IS NULL) AS cnt_null

            FROM dbt_db.dbt_schema.data_generator_enriched_describe

            GROUP BY ALL
            LIMIT 10
        ) ,
    
        column_detail_COUNTRY AS (
            SELECT
                1
                
                    , COUNTRY
                    , COUNT(*) AS cnt
                


                , SUM(COUNT(COUNTRY)) OVER () AS cnt_total
                , SUM(COUNT(DISTINCT COUNTRY)) OVER () AS cnt_unique
                , COUNT_IF(COUNTRY IS NULL) AS cnt_null

            FROM dbt_db.dbt_schema.data_generator_enriched_describe

            GROUP BY ALL
            LIMIT 10
        ) 
    

    
    , column_detail_info_text AS (
        
        SELECT
            'COMPANY_NAME' AS column_name
            , OBJECT_CONSTRUCT(
                'column_name', 'COMPANY_NAME'
                , 'count' , MIN(cnt_total)
                , 'count_null' , MIN(cnt_null)
                
                    , 'unique' , MIN(cnt_unique)
                    , 'value_counts_top10',OBJECT_AGG(COMPANY_NAME, cnt)
                
            ) AS detail
        FROM column_detail_COMPANY_NAME
        UNION ALL
    
        SELECT
            'COUNTRY' AS column_name
            , OBJECT_CONSTRUCT(
                'column_name', 'COUNTRY'
                , 'count' , MIN(cnt_total)
                , 'count_null' , MIN(cnt_null)
                
                    , 'unique' , MIN(cnt_unique)
                    , 'value_counts_top10',OBJECT_AGG(COUNTRY, cnt)
                
            ) AS detail
        FROM column_detail_COUNTRY
        
    

    )


    , 

    
    

    

    

    
    

    
    
        column_detail_STR_LENGTH AS (
            SELECT
                1
                
                    , AVG(STR_LENGTH) AS avg
                    , MIN(STR_LENGTH) AS min
                    , MAX(STR_LENGTH) AS max
                    
                    , APPROX_PERCENTILE(STR_LENGTH, 0.25) AS percentile_25
                    , APPROX_PERCENTILE(STR_LENGTH, 0.5) AS percentile_50
                    , APPROX_PERCENTILE(STR_LENGTH, 0.75) AS percentile_75
                    
                


                , SUM(COUNT(STR_LENGTH)) OVER () AS cnt_total
                , SUM(COUNT(DISTINCT STR_LENGTH)) OVER () AS cnt_unique
                , COUNT_IF(STR_LENGTH IS NULL) AS cnt_null

            FROM dbt_db.dbt_schema.data_generator_enriched_describe

            GROUP BY ALL
            LIMIT 10
        ) 
    

    
    , column_detail_info_numeric AS (
        
        SELECT
            'STR_LENGTH' AS column_name
            , OBJECT_CONSTRUCT(
                'column_name', 'STR_LENGTH'
                , 'count' , MIN(cnt_total)
                , 'count_null' , MIN(cnt_null)
                
                    , 'mean' , MIN(avg)
                    , 'min' , MIN(min)
                    , 'max' , MIN(max)
                    , 'percentile_25' , MIN(percentile_25)
                    , 'percentile_50' , MIN(percentile_50)
                    , 'percentile_75' , MIN(percentile_75)
                
            ) AS detail
        FROM column_detail_STR_LENGTH
        
    

    )


    SELECT
        assembed_result.meta_data_key
        , assembed_result.meta_data_value
        , assembed_result.identifier
        , COALESCE(text_detail.detail, numeric_detail.detail) AS detail
    FROM assembled_result AS assembed_result
    LEFT JOIN column_detail_info_text AS text_detail
    ON assembed_result.meta_data_key = text_detail.column_name
    LEFT JOIN column_detail_info_numeric AS numeric_detail
    ON assembed_result.meta_data_key = numeric_detail.column_name

    ORDER BY index_pos ASC


)
SELECT * FROM describe_dataframe
WHERE
    identifier = 'column'
    AND
    (
        (
            LOWER(meta_data_value) = 'text'

            AND (

                detail IS NULL

                OR (
                    meta_data_key = 'COMPANY_NAME' AND (

                    OR DETAIL:count::integer <> 54800
                    OR DETAIL:count_null::integer <> 0

                    OR DETAIL:value_counts_top10:AMZN::int <> 10960
